analysis.title: Global Market Outlook
analysis.content: Neutral stance persists amid mounting tariff risk. The GMS score of 52 dictates a transitionary regime where equity appreciation is increasingly decoupled from negative breadth. While the VIX exhibits compression, the appreciation in precious metals signals an emergent hedging mandate against the fiscal-monetary nexus and tariff-induced inflationary shocks. Despite liquidity stability, degradation in Asian indices suggests a bifurcated global growth trajectory requiring tactical caution. [ACTION: WAIT FOR PULLBACK]
